description: Agents Wade and Flynn investigate a settlement where a fear-mongering preacher named von Becker has seized control amid a crisis - the dead arising as super-strong and devilishly red-skinned zombies. Get on board with what indiepulp.com calles 'perhaps the best sleeper horror comic book today.'

Zombies, federal agents, the Old West - devour one of the most acclaimed indie titles of 2010! Are Ezekiel's settler's possessed by Satan? Agents Wade and Flynn race to find out what's killing them - and bringing them back super-strong and red-skinned - while a familiar-looking charlatan preacher named Father von Becker stokes the terror for his own fame!

An average night in Nalus City, three friends Asper, Kaylin and Richie search out a quiet place to rest within the noise of the city. Looking upon the metropolis from their rooftop-resting place, they realize that they have box seats to an illegal robot battle tournament, which is taking place in a nearby aboveground parking complex. Join the three as they witness the main event in the underground world of battle bots and gambling.

When Asper doesn't show up for dinner, Kaylin makes her way to his auto shop with his dinner in hand. When she arrives at the shop, she finds that it has been taken over by Asian gangsters and turned into a battle location for the U.B.B. Hiding in the front row to a rumble of lightweight robot's, Kaylin learns some of the inner workings of the U.B.B. organization and just who is behind the scenes.

Asper and Nicky head deep into old Chinatown to pay a visit to Uncle Moon, Rolly's boss and a known member of the criminal organization 'The Lotuz Society'. But, upon their visit, a member of the UBB recognizes Asper. A call is made and minutes later the two find themselves cornered in an alley by an unfriendly group of thugs with no choice but to fight their way out.

Ain't We Having Fun Yet?

At Knock Uppe University, Ralph sheds his major geekness, joins a band and gets drunk and stupid. Meanwhile, in "reality", Ralph's brain eludes Dr. Goot.

Idiots From Space

Ralph's brain attacks its creator and runs amok, while in his dreamworld, Ralph battles hungry, booze-chugging aliens, and an even worse foe, his blind date from Hell.
